Class QueryExecutionOptions

java.lang.Object
  com.versant.fund.QueryExecutionOptions

public class QueryExecutionOptions
extends java.lang.Object

An instance of this class encapsulates the options that can be defined for the execution of a com.versant.trans.Query instance.

isFetchObjects

public boolean isFetchObjects()

Returns:

setFetchObjects

public QueryExecutionOptions setFetchObjects(boolean fetchObjects)
Determines whether all retrieved objects should be fetched to the client cache immediately. The precise meaning depends on the fetch size of the query:

If no fetch size or a non-positive fetch size is set, all objects that satisfy the query are fetched into the client object cache in a single group operation.

However, positive fetch size values allow query execution in multiple steps (cursor batches). The query execution in the database is continued transparently, when the objects of a batch have been consumed during iteration over the query result on the client site. In this case, the option fetch-objects means, that each batch of objects is fetched into the client cache in one single group operation.

Parameters:
fetchObjects - if true all retrieved objects will be fetched to the client cache immediately
Returns:
this instance
See Also:
FundQuery.setFetchSize(int), Query.setFetchSize(int)

setFlushAll

public QueryExecutionOptions setFlushAll(boolean flushAll)
If set, the query will flush all new and dirty objects from the client cache first before executing the query in the server.

This option is not compatible with flush-none and will unset that option if set.

Parameters:
flushAll -
Returns:

isFlushNone

public boolean isFlushNone()

Returns:
true if flush-none is set.

setFlushNone

public QueryExecutionOptions setFlushNone(boolean flushNone)
If set, the query will flush no new and dirty objects from the client cache first before executing the query in the server. New and dirty objects that have not been flushed to the database and fulfill the predicate might therefore not be in the result set.

This option is not compatible with flush-all and will unset that option if set.

Parameters:
flushNone -
Returns:
The instance.
